article.description: — Jordan Walker scored 32 points and UAB beat North Texas 76-69 on Friday night in the Conference USA Tournament for its eighth straight victory.
article.headline: Walker's 32 lead UAB over North Texas in C-USA tourney
article.linkText: Walker's 32 lead UAB over North Texas in C-USA tourney
article.story:
FRISCO, Texas -- — Jordan Walker scored 32 points and UAB beat North Texas 76-69 on Friday night in the Conference USA Tournament for its eighth straight victory.

Walker also had six rebounds and six assists for the Blazers (25-8). KJ Buffen scored 13 points and added seven rebounds. Javian Davis shot 3 of 4 from the field and 5 for 7 from the line to finish with 11 points.

Tylor Perry led the way for the Mean Green (26-7) with 17 points. Kai Huntsberry added 14 points, four assists and two steals for North Texas. Aaron Scott also put up 13 points, 13 rebounds and two blocks.

------
